Title: Segregatory Coordination and Ellipsis in Text Generation  
Author: James Shaw 
Address: New York, NY 10027, USA  
Affiliation: Dept. of Computer Science Columbia University  
Note: Published in Proc. of COLING-ACL, 1998.  
Abstract: In this paper, we provide an account of how to generate sentences with coordination constructions from clause-sized semantic representations. An algorithm is developed and various examples from linguistic literature will be used to demonstrate that the algorithm does its job well. 
